tifier": "kent-maury-1988758", "recommendations/0/context": "Kent worked with Ken on the same team", "recommendations/0/date": "November 27, 2014", "recommendations/0/description": "Ken Wong's work ethic, integrity and professionalism are just a few of his \nmany positive characteristics. He is focused on the hospitality business \nand brings great value to the companies with whom he has been associated.\n\nKen's ability to motivate team members, interact with customers and stay \ngrounded in what makes sales and marketing successful is paramount to \nensuring positive financial, associate and business results.\n\nWhen we worked together, he was an integral part of the Marriott Sales / \nMarketing Team and brought expertise, experience and knowledge into all \naspects of the business. I believe Ken Wong to be an excellent associate \nand would welcome the opportunity to work with him again.\n\nKent Maury\nRegional V.P. Sales and Marketing Asia Pacific (former)", "recommendations/0/name": "Ken Wong", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Tourism | Attractions | Entertainment |Hospitality", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ken-wong-1541928a/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABLkU1ABM0Xl6DAS3Ur_7GCpsr9kO-i7jE4", "recommendations/1/context": "Kent was senior to Mark but didn't manage Mark directly", "recommendations/1/date": "July 5, 2013", "recommendations/1/description": "Mark Cunningham is a born leader ... gaining the respect of colleagues and clients across various cultures and situations. His ability to move from Japan to India (as an example) in Marriott leadership positions, and to be so successful in his endeavors, is an endorsement of mark's style, ability, cultural sensitivity, knowledge and personality. I would place Mark at the top of any leadership and competence scale. He is a great asset to any organization with whom he is affiliated.", "recommendations/1/name": "Mark C.", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Regional Vice President of Operations & Sales", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/markjcunningham/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFLFqQBXlRKx0i2xhazQe1E5ZwUn2DHQSw", "recommendations/2/context": "Kent worked with Nicholas on the same team", "recommendations/2/date": "February 4, 2013", "recommendations/2/description": "As General Manager of the Sky City Marriott in Hong Kong, Nick Tse's focus, dedication, marketing / sales skills, ability to motivate staff and clear direction turned this property around to become a showcase on how to effectively manage a hotel.  Through setting individual and collective goals, developing a positive owner's relationship, leveraging Marriott's systems and taking care of his associates and his guests, Nick Tse garnered recognition with not only actual awards but also from his piers and senior management. To have this man on your team is an insurance policy for success. Kent Maury", "recommendations/2/name": "Nicholas Tse  FIH", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Award-Winning Hotel Management Strategies", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholastsemih/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADApscBkMr8Uu9SIe6ii4pxcq7goC5FpBo", "recommendations/3/context": "Kent was senior to Ellen but didn't manage Ellen directly", "recommendations/3/date": "December 18, 2012", "recommendations/3/description": "As a former associate of Ellen Fu, and someone who worked closely with her during our tenure at Marriott International, I can say without equivocation that she is a focused, conscientious and hard working individual. Her professionalism and dedication to her job and the desire to move the business forward have always been trademarks of Ellen. Her goal is to achieve the maximum for and to ensure the company's success while delivering on the promises made to customers. Ms. Fu has the ability to maintain existing accounts while at the same time identifying new potential customers.  Her outgoing personality ensures that her relationship with all colleagues is on the highest plane and she is a well respected associate of the company.  I certainly would recommend Ellen Fu to a company interested in employing her and would be happy to do so personally.", "recommendations/3/name": "Ellen Fu", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "COO | Corporate Entrepreneur | CK Hutchison | Digital Transformation & Ecosystem Builder | ex-Samsung", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ellenfu/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADlD14BXnse7Sa2MYAftSjj5G7EwfGOFIo", "recommendations/4/context": "Kent was senior to Jonathan but didn't manage Jonathan directly", "recommendations/4/date": "April 6, 2011", "recommendations/4/description": "What a pleasure to write a recommendation for Jonathan Low. \n\nWe worked together at Marriott International; Jonathan was responsible for ensuring proper Revenue Management techniques and strategies were implemented at hotels within his geographical area of responsibility. The proper techniques and strategy for the respective individual hotels would ensure greater profitability and a positive increase in owner, associate and Marriott relationships. To achieve this goal Jonathan also was responsible for training of associates - he excelled in this responsibiliy.\nJonathan worked well with the individual hotels and contributed a great deal knowledge to the Area Team which oversaw South East Asia. His attention to detail, inter-personal skills and knowledge helped the Area hotels increase REVPAR, profitablity and in turn Marriott's expansion in the Area. Jonathan actively participated in strategy sessions, positively challenged the people above him as well as his Revenue Management reports and helped develop the \"best course of action\" that benefited all parties. \nIf someone reading this is looking for a team-player, a good man who knows his stuff and someone to bring value to an organization, Jonathan Low is your person.", "recommendations/4/name": "Jonathan Low, Global Speaking Fellow, CSP, MCC, GCMC", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Transforming Global & Regional Organizations | Conf Keynote Speaker & Global Chief Master Coach | Leadership Development •Sales Excellence • Service Quality I Global Speaking Fellow | 43+ Countries I MG 100Coaches", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathanlow/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABWT64Be0nA-bQzXXyS252H4BB57RPwL_Q", "recommendations/5/context": "Kent worked with Norma on the same team", "recommendations/5/date": "January 20, 2011", "recommendations/5/description": "Norma Tomkinson is a detailed oriented and focused individual whose attention to detail ensures that her projects, her recommendations and her follow-up is excellent. One would find Norma extremely reliable and when she makes a commitment - consider it done. Her strong desire to succeed means she generally does. She is an excellent coach and counsellor.", "recommendations/5/name": "Norma Tomkinson", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Independent Hospitality Professional with experience in sales, marketing and revenue management.", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/normatomkinson/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGMEjABdqCuTE1idkegSh4E-RcTQQq41L0", "recommendations/6/context": "Kent worked with David on the same team", "recommendations/6/date": "February 24, 2010", "recommendations/6/description": "David Kasten is the ultimate professional. His knowledge of accounting and finance makes him an asset to any organization; more especially because David is there to help / assist non finance departments to understand the \"whole picture\" and the importance of finance to ensure a successful operation. He relates positively to others, he communicates well and he helps to move the business forward. From a sales / marketing standpoint David is an excellent resource and knows / appreciates the need of finance and sales to work together to maximize revenues and profits. He is a mentor; has an open-door policy; he is approachable; a man of great integrity and a team player. This man would be a large contributor to the success of any business.", "recommendations/6/name": "David Kasten", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "CFO/COO Hospitality Management; Asset Management; Private Equity", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidekasten/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACx93UBIaWJnVwIkPDns7YklGccbLeEhcA", "recommendations/7/context": "Kent worked with Alex on the same team", "recommendations/7/date": "May 4, 2009", "recommendations/7/description": "Alex Ang is an individual with numerous talents and lots of energy who is focused on ensuring all associates receive the proper training necessary to carry out their responsibilities and to move forward in the organization. I recognized this when he was head of HR at the Renaissance Hotel Suzhou when training was conducted at the property during the pre-opening period. His professionalism and his ability to work in a multi-tier environment brings value and learning to associates which in-turn translates into guest satisfaction. He appreciates the culture of a company (as well as the culture of a specific society or country which must always be taken into consideration) and how that is conveyed from associate to guest which ensures repeat business - which was accomplished during the opening of the Renaissance Suzhou.. Alex is hard working, a participative team player and dedicated to success as Asia Pacific - Starwood Hotels & Resorts as Director of Organisational Learning & Culture would soon determine.", "recommendations/7/name": "Alex A.", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Dynamic and Strategic Leader | Organizational Change Champion | HR Expert", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/angalex/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAH5XVMBGxtXaNH4LACbd_XhZLmWSr_4Pew", "skil