ve itineraries/excursions/activities, setup menus with our Head Chef, create drinks list including traditional and signature cocktails, give guide lines to our Training Manager, to make guiding research and train our guides on board, to assist for the decoration of the cruise center and all vessels, support the Operation Department, work closely with marketing on branded souvenirs, improve the sales on board, participate on creation of events with our MICE department. \nAlso in charge of the safety, I conducted weekly emergency drills and trained the crew of different cases of emergency could happens anytime, hygiene audits and training was a must to maintain a great service.", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "9-2015", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Ha Long Bay - Vietnam", "experiences/5/jobLocationCountry": "VN", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "5-2013", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQFk-SINCYqy5A/company-logo_400_400/B4DZYevTEQHIAg-/0/1744272438017/bhaya_cruises_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=-F9F1UsjwVC4FziZsII_0EjrW1DfmR_AmQs4oylIytU", "experiences/5/title": "Quality Control Manager", "experiences/6/companyName": "Phi Phi the beach resort", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "Located on the best \"Long Beach\" of the famous Koh Phi Phi Island, I was on charge of the F&B in Phi Phi The Beach Resort. \nAt my start, the Beach Restaurant wasn't popular and only few guests per day.\nI set up new disposition, trained the team members, re-organized the kitchen, worked with the chef to make new menu, created a Daily Seafood BBQ with huge range of fresh selection, made the beverages and cocktail lists, set up a new buffet for the breakfast.\nThe 2 first years we had also Lunch Buffet, hosting 200-400 guests coming only for the lunch during their day trip in the island.\nI also was in charge of the events such as private dinners, weddings on the beach, celebration of xmas and new years gala dinners with show & entertainment for 200 persons.\nI created weekly themes in the restaurant as the average stay of the guests was 10 days.\nAfter only few months, the Beach restaurant was full every days, hosting as well people coming from other resorts.\nBeside I was in charge of the guests relation, handle complains and solved problems. I must work closely with all departments for a best guest's satisfaction.\nVery close to the owners I was working with them and the marketing manager in a great team. I can say I was working more as operations for the resort, not only for the f&B department.", "experiences/6/jobEndedOn": "1-2013", "experiences/6/jobLocation": "koh Phi Phi, Thailand", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "11-2008", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/6/title": "F&B manager and Guest Relation", "experiences/7/companyName": "Hi.So", "experiences/7/jobDescription": "I owned a Restaurant Bar Lounge Gallery (400m2), Created all design decorations and follow their fabrications, the place was branded \"most beautiful gallery of south Thailand\".\nI made the interior decoration, created all menus F&B, MICE events for parties, fashion shows, live bands, themes, sales & marketing.", "experiences/7/jobEndedOn": "2013", "experiences/7/jobStartedOn": "2010", "experiences/7/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/7/title": "CEO & Designer", "experiences/8/companyName": "Le Rendez-Vous Hotel", "experiences/8/jobDescription": "Boutique hotel in touristic area, I managed the operations with all departments, I created, designed & managed the bar/restaurant, work closely with the marketing team for the event, tours and packages.", "experiences/8/jobEndedOn": "10-2008", "experiences/8/jobStartedOn": "6-2006", "experiences/8/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/8/title": "Resident Manager", "experiences/9/companyName": "Murphy's House", "experiences/9/jobDescription": "Franchised restaurant with a capacity of 300 seats on 4 floors, I managed all operations, changed the a